&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;There has never been a better time to join our team; working within our nurse led &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Pre-Operative Assessment Service (POAS), &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;will enable you to develop &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;valuable clinical skills to include; collating histories, assessments, clinical decision making and phlebotomy. There are also opportunities to undertake link nurse roles and participate in service development projects and away days.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our service is responsible for assessing, screening and preparing all adult elective surgical patients prior to surgery. We help to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;reduce complications, lengths of stay, and long-term morbidity and mortality by:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;•&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Risk assessment and stratification&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;•&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Optimisation of comorbidities and lifestyle to reduce risk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;•&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shared, informed decision-making&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;•&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Triaging patients to receive the appropriate resources to support their recovery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;•&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Pre-anaesthesia screening &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous surgical or acute experience is advantageous; however, you will receive a supernumerary period and be supported by in-house training and a competency document.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;With your passion for quality care and previous pre-operative assessment and/or surgical experience, you will enjoy the chance to play a key role in supporting the delivery of high quality pre-operative care, now and in the future. In return for your dedication, determination and enthusiasm, we will assist you with your own personal career development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an autonomous role in a busy, innovative, nurse-led department which operates 7 days a week and offers opportunities to rotate across both of our sites:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;University Hospital Coventry &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Hospital of St Cross, Rugby&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal chat or to arrange a visit, please contact Claire Badger, Consultant Nurse Lead Pre-Operative Service on 024 7696 4000 or extension 25893.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
